{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"This is very strange for me, because I’m not used to doing this:"},{"time":3000,"text":"I usually stand on the other side of the light,"},{"time":6000,"text":"and now I'm feeling the pressure I put other people into. And it's hard ..."},{"time":13000,"text":"The previous speaker has, I think,"},{"time":16000,"text":"really painted a very good background as to"},{"time":22000,"text":"the impulse behind my work and what drives me, and my sense of loss,"},{"time":28000,"text":"and trying to find the answer to the big questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34000,"text":"But this, for me, I mean, coming here to do this,"},{"time":39000,"text":"feels like -- there’s this sculptor that I like very much, Giacometti,"},{"time":47000,"text":"who after many years of living in France -- and learning, you know,"},{"time":52000,"text":"studying and working -- he returned home and he was asked, what did you produce?"},{"time":59000,"text":"What have you done with so many years of being away?"},{"time":63000,"text":"And he sort of, he showed a handful of figurines."},{"time":66000,"text":"And obviously they were, \"Is this what you spent years doing?"},{"time":71000,"text":"And we expected huge masterpieces!\""},{"time":76000,"text":"But what struck me is the understanding that in those little pieces"},{"time":82000,"text":"was the culmination of a man’s life, search, thought, everything --"},{"time":88000,"text":"just in a reduced, small version."},{"time":90000,"text":"In a way, I feel like that."},{"time":92000,"text":"I feel like I’m coming home to talk about"},{"time":95000,"text":"what I’ve been away doing for 20 years."},{"time":99000,"text":"And I will start with a brief taster of what I’ve been about:"},{"time":105000,"text":"a handful of films -- nothing much,"},{"time":107000,"text":"two feature films and a handful of short films."},{"time":110000,"text":"So, we’ll go with the first piece."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114000,"text":"(Video) Woman: \"I destroy lives,\" mum said."},{"time":123000,"text":"I love her, you know."},{"time":127000,"text":"She’s not even my real mum."},{"time":129000,"text":"My real mum and dad dumped me"},{"time":133000,"text":"and fucked off back to Nigeria."},{"time":140000,"text":"The devil is in me, Court."},{"time":144000,"text":"Court: Sleep."},{"time":148000,"text":"Woman: Have you ever been?"},{"time":150000,"text":"Court: Where?"},{"time":152000,"text":"Woman: Nigeria."},{"time":156000,"text":"Court: Never."},{"time":158000,"text":"My mum wanted to,"},{"time":161000,"text":"couldn’t afford it."},{"time":164000,"text":"Woman: Wish I could."},{"time":166000,"text":"I have this feeling I’d be happy there."},{"time":176000,"text":"Why does everyone get rid of me?"},{"time":180000,"text":"Court: I don't want to get rid of you."},{"time":182000,"text":"Woman: You don't need me."},{"time":186000,"text":"You’re just too blind to see it now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191000,"text":"Boy: What do you do all day?"},{"time":195000,"text":"Marcus: Read."},{"time":197000,"text":"Boy: Don't you get bored?"},{"time":199000,"text":"And how come you ain't got a job anyway?"},{"time":202000,"text":"Marcus: I am retired."},{"time":204000,"text":"Boy: So?"},{"time":206000,"text":"Marcus: So I've done my bit for Queen and country, now I work for myself."},{"time":209000,"text":"Boy: No, now you sit around like a bum all day."},{"time":211000,"text":"Marcus: Because I do what I like?"},{"time":214000,"text":"Boy: Look man, reading don't feed no one."},{"time":216000,"text":"And it particularly don't feed your spliff habit."},{"time":218000,"text":"Marcus: It feeds my mind and my soul."},{"time":222000,"text":"Boy: Arguing with you is a waste of time, Marcus."},{"time":229000,"text":"Marcus: You’re a rapper, am I right?"},{"time":231000,"text":"Boy: Yeah."},{"time":232000,"text":"Marcus: A modern day poet."},{"time":233000,"text":"Boy: Yeah, you could say that."},{"time":234000,"text":"Marcus: So what do you talk about?"},{"time":236000,"text":"Boy: What's that supposed to mean?"},{"time":238000,"text":"Marcus: Simple. What do you rap about?"},{"time":240000,"text":"Boy: Reality, man."},{"time":242000,"text":"Marcus: Whose reality?"},{"time":243000,"text":"Boy: My fuckin' reality."},{"time":245000,"text":"Marcus: Tell me about your reality."},{"time":247000,"text":"Boy: Racism, oppression, people like me not getting a break in life."},{"time":251000,"text":"Marcus: So what solutions do you offer? I mean, the job of a poet is not just --"},{"time":254000,"text":"Boy: Man, fight the power! Simple: blow the motherfuckers out of the sky."},{"time":257000,"text":"Marcus: With an AK-47?"},{"time":258000,"text":"Boy: Man, if I had one, too fuckin' right."},{"time":260000,"text":"Marcus: And how many soldiers have you recruited to fight this war with you?"},{"time":263000,"text":"Boy: Oh, Marcus, you know what I mean."},{"time":266000,"text":"Marcus: When a man resorts to profanities,"},{"time":268000,"text":"it’s a sure sign of his inability to express himself."},{"time":272000,"text":"Boy: See man, you’re just taking the piss out of me now."},{"time":275000,"text":"Marcus: The Panthers."},{"time":277000,"text":"Boy: Panthers?"},{"time":278000,"text":"Ass kickin' guys who were fed up with all that white supremacist, powers-that-be bullshit,"},{"time":282000,"text":"and just went in there and kicked everybody's arse."},{"time":285000,"text":"Fuckin’ wicked, man. I saw the movie. Bad! What?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":289000,"text":"Director 1: I saw his last film."},{"time":293000,"text":"Épuise, right?"},{"time":295000,"text":"Woman 1: Yes."},{"time":296000,"text":"D1: Not to make a bad joke, but it was really épuisé."},{"time":303000,"text":"Epuisé -- tired, exhausted, fed up."},{"time":310000,"text":"Director 2: Can you not shut up?"},{"time":312000,"text":"Now, you talk straight to me, what’s wrong with my films?"},{"time":314000,"text":"Let’s go."},{"time":316000,"text":"W1: They suck."},{"time":317000,"text":"Woman 2: They suck? What about yours?"},{"time":320000,"text":"What, what, what, what about, what?"},{"time":323000,"text":"What do you think about your movie?"},{"time":325000,"text":"D1: My movies, they are OK, fine."},{"time":327000,"text":"They are better than making documentaries no one ever sees."},{"time":330000,"text":"What the fuck are you talking about?"},{"time":332000,"text":"Did you ever move your fuckin' ass from Hollywood"},{"time":335000,"text":"to go and film something real?"},{"time":337000,"text":"You make people fuckin' sleep."},{"time":339000,"text":"Dream about bullshit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":345000,"text":"Newton Aduaka: Thank you. The first clip, really, is"},{"time":350000,"text":"totally trying to capture what cinema is for me,"},{"time":354000,"text":"and where I'm coming from in terms of cinema."},{"time":356000,"text":"The first piece was, really, there's a young woman talking about Nigeria,"},{"time":361000,"text":"that she has a feeling she'll be happy there."},{"time":364000,"text":"These are the sentiments of someone that's been away from home."},{"time":367000,"text":"And that was something that I went through, you know, and I'm still going through."},{"time":370000,"text":"I've not been home for quite a while, for about five years now."},{"time":373000,"text":"I've been away 20 years in total."},{"time":377000,"text":"And so it’s really --"},{"time":380000,"text":"it's really how suddenly, you know, this was made in 1997,"},{"time":386000,"text":"which is the time of Abacha -- the military dictatorship,"},{"time":390000,"text":"the worst part of Nigerian history, this post-colonial history."},{"time":395000,"text":"So, for this girl to have these dreams"},{"time":397000,"text":"is simply how we preserve a sense of what home is."},{"time":401000,"text":"How -- and it's sort of, perhaps romantic, but I think beautiful,"},{"time":407000,"text":"because you just need something to hold on to,"},{"time":411000,"text":"especially in a society where you feel alienated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"Which takes us to the next piece, where the young man"},{"time":417000,"text":"talks about lack of opportunity: living as a black person in Europe,"},{"time":423000,"text":"the glass ceiling that we all know about, that we all talk about,"},{"time":427000,"text":"and his reality."},{"time":431000,"text":"Again, this was my -- this was me talking about --"},{"time":433000,"text":"this was, again, the time of multiculturalism in the United Kingdom,"},{"time":437000,"text":"and there was this buzzword -- and it was trying to say,"},{"time":440000,"text":"what exactly does this multiculturalism mean in the real lives of people?"},{"time":444000,"text":"And what would a child --"},{"time":447000,"text":"what does a child like Jamie -- the young boy -- think,"},{"time":450000,"text":"I mean, with all this anger that's built up inside of him?"},{"time":454000,"text":"What happens with that?"},{"time":456000,"text":"What, of course, happens with that is violence,"},{"time":458000,"text":"which we see when we talk about the ghettos"},{"time":462000,"text":"and we talk about, you know, South Central L.A. and this kind of stuff,"},{"time":466000,"text":"and which eventually, when channeled, becomes,"},{"time":469000,"text":"you know, evolves and manifests itself as riots --"},{"time":474000,"text":"like the one in France two years ago, where I live,"},{"time":478000,"text":"which shocked everybody, because everyone thought, \"Oh well,"},{"time":480000,"text":"France is a liberal society.\""},{"time":482000,"text":"But I lived in England for 18 years."},{"time":485000,"text":"I've lived in France for about four, and I feel actually"},{"time":488000,"text":"thrown back 20 years, living in France."},{"time":493000,"text":"And then, the third piece. The third piece for me is the question:"},{"time":496000,"text":"What is cinema to you? What do you do with cinema?"},{"time":499000,"text":"There's a young director, Hollywood director, with his friends --"},{"time":507000,"text":"fellow filmmakers -- talking about what cinema means."},{"time":510000,"text":"I suppose that will take me to my last piece --"},{"time":514000,"text":"what cinema means for me."},{"time":516000,"text":"My life started as a -- I started life in 1966,"},{"time":520000,"text":"a few months before the Biafran, which lasted for three years"},{"time":523000,"text":"and it was three years of war."},{"time":525000,"text":"So that whole thing,"},{"time":528000,"text":"that whole childhood echoes and takes me into the next piece."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544000,"text":"(Video) Voice: Onicha, off to school with your brother."},{"time":547000,"text":"Onicha: Yes, mama."},{"time":597000,"text":"Commander: Soldiers, you are going to fight a battle,"},{"time":604000,"text":"so you must get ready and willing to die."},{"time":607000,"text":"You must get -- ?"},{"time":608000,"text":"Child Soldiers: Ready and willing to die."},{"time":611000,"text":"C: Success, the change is only coming through the barrel of the gun."},{"time":617000,"text":"CS: The barrel of the gun!"},{"time":619000,"text":"C: This is the gun."},{"time":620000,"text":"CS: This is the gun."},{"time":624000,"text":"C: This is an AK-47 rifle. This is your life."},{"time":626000,"text":"This is your life. This is ... this is ... this is your life."},{"time":632000,"text":"Ezra: They give us the special drugs. We call it bubbles."},{"time":635000,"text":"Amphetamines."},{"time":638000,"text":"Soldiers: Rain come, sun come, soldier man dey go."},{"time":641000,"text":"I say rain come, sun come, soldier man dey go."},{"time":644000,"text":"We went from one village to another -- three villages."},{"time":646000,"text":"I don’t remember how we got there."},{"time":648000,"text":"Witness: We walked and walked for two days."},{"time":651000,"text":"We didn't eat."},{"time":653000,"text":"There was no food, just little rice."},{"time":657000,"text":"Without food -- I was sick."},{"time":659000,"text":"The injection made us not to have mind."},{"time":662000,"text":"God will forgive us."},{"time":664000,"text":"He knows we did not know. We did not know!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":683000,"text":"Committee Chairman: Do you remember January 6th, 1999?"},{"time":688000,"text":"Ezra: I don’t remember."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690000,"text":"Various Voices: You will die! You will die! (Screaming)"},{"time":693000,"text":"Onicha: Ezra! (Ezra: Onicha! Onicha!)"},{"time":695000,"text":"Various Voices: ♫ We don't need no more trouble ♫"},{"time":703000,"text":"♫ No more trouble ♫"},{"time":705000,"text":"They killed my mother."},{"time":707000,"text":"The Mende sons of bastards."},{"time":709000,"text":"(Shouting)"},{"time":712000,"text":"Who is she?"},{"time":714000,"text":"Me."},{"time":715000,"text":"Why you giving these to me?"},{"time":716000,"text":"So you can stop staring at me."},{"time":719000,"text":"My story is a little bit complicated."},{"time":722000,"text":"I’m interested."},{"time":724000,"text":"Mariam is pregnant."},{"time":726000,"text":"You know what you are? A crocodile."},{"time":728000,"text":"Big mouth. Short legs."},{"time":733000,"text":"In front of Rufus you are Ezra the coward."},{"time":735000,"text":"He’s not taking care of his troops."},{"time":737000,"text":"Troop, pay your last honor. Salute."},{"time":742000,"text":"Open your eyes, Ezra."},{"time":744000,"text":"A blind man can see that the diamonds end up in his pocket."},{"time":746000,"text":"♫ We don't need no more trouble ♫"},{"time":755000,"text":"Get that idiot out!"},{"time":758000,"text":"I take you are preparing a major attack?"},{"time":761000,"text":"This must be the mine."},{"time":763000,"text":"Your girl is here."},{"time":764000,"text":"Well done, well done."},{"time":769000,"text":"That is what you are here for, no?"},{"time":771000,"text":"You are planning to go back to fight are you?"},{"time":774000,"text":"♫ We don't need no more trouble ♫"},{"time":781000,"text":"♫ No more trouble ♫"},{"time":783000,"text":"♫ We don't need no more trouble ♫"},{"time":793000,"text":"♫ No more trouble. ♫"},{"time":796000,"text":"Wake up! Everybody wake up. Road block!"},{"time":799000,"text":"♫ We don't need no more ... ♫"}]},{"cues":[{"time":828000,"text":"Committee Chairman: We hope that, with your help and the help of others, that this commission"},{"time":833000,"text":"will go a long way towards understanding the causes of the rebel war."},{"time":838000,"text":"More than that, begin a healing process and finally to --"},{"time":840000,"text":"as an act of closure to a terrible period in this country’s history."},{"time":846000,"text":"The beginning of hope."},{"time":847000,"text":"Mr. Ezra Gelehun, please stand."},{"time":859000,"text":"State your name and age for the commission."},{"time":864000,"text":"Ezra: My name is Ezra Gelehun."},{"time":866000,"text":"I am 15 or 16. I don’t remember."},{"time":870000,"text":"Ask my sister, she is the witch, she knows everything."},{"time":875000,"text":"(Sister: 16.)"},{"time":880000,"text":"CC: Mr. Gelehun, I’d like to remind you you’re not on trial here"},{"time":883000,"text":"for any crimes you committed."},{"time":885000,"text":"E: We were fighting for our freedom."},{"time":887000,"text":"If killing in a war is a crime,"},{"time":890000,"text":"then you have to charge every soldier in the world."},{"time":894000,"text":"War is a crime, yes, but I did not start it."},{"time":898000,"text":"You too are a retired General, not so?"},{"time":902000,"text":"CC: Yes, correct."},{"time":904000,"text":"E: So you too must stand trial then."},{"time":906000,"text":"Our government was corrupt."},{"time":910000,"text":"Lack of education was their way to control power."},{"time":915000,"text":"If I may ask, do you pay for school in your country?"},{"time":918000,"text":"CC: No, we don’t."},{"time":923000,"text":"E: You are richer than us."},{"time":925000,"text":"But we pay for school."},{"time":929000,"text":"Your country talks about democracy,"},{"time":931000,"text":"but you support corrupt governments like my own."},{"time":935000,"text":"Why? Because you want our diamond."},{"time":938000,"text":"Ask if anyone in this room have ever seen real diamond before?"},{"time":942000,"text":"No."},{"time":944000,"text":"CC: Mr. Gelehun, I'd like to remind you, you're not on trial here today."},{"time":950000,"text":"You are not on trial."},{"time":951000,"text":"E: Then let me go."},{"time":954000,"text":"CC: I can't do that, son."},{"time":957000,"text":"E: So you are a liar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":961000,"text":"NA: Thank you. Just very quickly to say that my point really here,"},{"time":964000,"text":"is that while we’re making all these huge advancements,"},{"time":966000,"text":"what we're doing, which for me, you know, I think we should --"},{"time":972000,"text":"Africa should move forward, but we should remember,"},{"time":976000,"text":"so we do not go back here again."},{"time":978000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":979000,"text":"Emeka Okafor: Thank you, Newton."}]},{"cues":[{"time":981000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":984000,"text":"One of the themes that comes through very strongly"},{"time":988000,"text":"in the piece we just watched is this sense of the psychological trauma of the young"},{"time":998000,"text":"that have to play this role of being child soldiers."},{"time":1003000,"text":"And considering where you are coming from,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"and when we consider the extent to which it’s not taken as seriously"},{"time":1013000,"text":"as it should be, what would you have to say about that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1017000,"text":"NA: In the process of my research, I actually spent"},{"time":1020000,"text":"a bit of time in Sierra Leone researching this."},{"time":1023000,"text":"And I remember I met a lot of child soldiers --"},{"time":1028000,"text":"ex-combatants, as they like to be called."},{"time":1034000,"text":"I met psychosocial workers who worked with them."},{"time":1039000,"text":"I met psychiatrists who spent time with them,"},{"time":1042000,"text":"aid workers, NGOs, the whole lot."},{"time":1045000,"text":"But I remember on the flight back on my last trip,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"I remember breaking down in tears and thinking to myself,"},{"time":1053000,"text":"if any kid in the West, in the western world,"},{"time":1059000,"text":"went through a day of what any of those kids have gone through,"},{"time":1064000,"text":"they will be in therapy for the rest of their natural lives."},{"time":1070000,"text":"So for me, the thought that we have all these children --"},{"time":1075000,"text":"it’s a generation, we have a whole generation of children --"},{"time":1078000,"text":"who have been put through so much psychological trauma or damage,"},{"time":1085000,"text":"and Africa has to live with that."},{"time":1087000,"text":"But I’m just saying to factor that in,"},{"time":1089000,"text":"factor that in with all this great advancement,"},{"time":1092000,"text":"all this pronouncement of great achievement."},{"time":1096000,"text":"That’s really my thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1098000,"text":"EO: Well, we thank you again for coming to the TED stage."},{"time":1101000,"text":"That was a very moving piece."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1103000,"text":"NA: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1104000,"text":"EO: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1105000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}